This paper is about evaluating and comparing statistical NLP systems, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of statistical methods for analyzing the distribution of performance figures, which could be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), information retrieval (cs.IR), and data structures (cs.DS).
